dcterms:description: A large annotated corpus for learning natural language inference, which allows end-to-end differentiable neural networks to outperform feature-based classifiers on the RTE task.
dcterms:title: Stanford Natural Language Inference (SNLI) corpus

dcterms:description: A dataset created by filtering the Stanford Natural Language Inference corpus for sentence-pairs of the entailment class, used for a sequence transduction task.
dcterms:title: Entailment generation dataset (derived from SNLI)
